abstract: >
  Pipeline code, prompt templates, configuration files, and documentation
  for the auditable LLM-DAG keyword harmonisation workflow described in
  El Majjaoui et al. (2026). The workflow formalises bibliometric keyword
  harmonisation as a pairwise concept-equivalence task with three constrained
  outputs (match / non-match / uncertain), a guard layer permitting principled
  abstention, and full provenance logging. Benchmarked against six baselines
  on a 500-pair gold-standard benchmark (kappa = 0.81, F1 = 0.965).
license: MIT
